#Tiny Adventures
# Author: jaybee@tiscali.co.za
#Based loosely on some of the Tiny Adventrures from the Facebook Application
#Credit/Kudus/etc to those guys who did a hell of a job generating all those adventures
#Checkout http://apps.facebook.com/tinyadventures/index.php
#
#As you can see the table starts by selecting the "main" adventure.
#The main adventure is divided into smaller encountersin various locations eg. Graveyards, Forests, Mountains, Tombs, etc.
#
# Compared to Tiny Adventures.tab this table has no reference to succes or fail of an encounter and what type of check was performed.
#
#
#There are thus main variables: Rescue the Princess (that gets generated in main adventure)
#and encounter variables: %PC_Name% sees a unicorm (that gets generated in encounter)
#
#I would like to at some point extent the encounters to be more random ie. with more generation included
#Also Adventures can be "extended" with a difficulty setting that will generate more encounters during the adventure.
#Once again refer to the Tiny Adventures app to see how this works
#
#Start and setup global varialbles

/OverrideRolls 1

#  Define Variables - Added August 2005
%Gender%,0
%PC_Gender%,0
%PC_Weapon%,0
%PC_Treasure%,0
%PC_Name%,0
%NPC_Gender%,0
%NPC_Name%,0
%NPC_Occupation%,0

%Relative%,0
%TempNumber%,0
%Chance%,0

@Gender,3,Choose gender,Male,Female,Random

# Gender Usage
# Use |Gender=%PC_Gender%| with [HimHer] or [ManWoman] or [HeShe] or [HisHer] 
# or for NPC's set gender with |NPC_Gender=1| or |2| and the use |Gender=%NPC_Gender%| with [HimHer] or [ManWoman] or [HeShe] or [HisHer]
# To capatilze  use {Cap~[HeShe]}
# Gender issues used from Background Sorcery.tab modified Valminder and Larry Cormier respectively
#

:Start
1,[Generate][Adventures]

:Gender
1,male
2,female

:ManWoman
1,{If~%Gender%=1?man/woman}

:HeShe
1,{If~%Gender%=1?he/she}

:HisHer
1,{If~%Gender%=1?his/her}

:HisHers
1,{If~%Gender%=1?his/hers}

:HimHer
1,{If~%Gender%=1?him/her}

:HimselfHerself
1,{If~%Gender%=1?himself/herself}

:Generate
1,{If~%Gender%=3?|Gender={Dice~1d2}|}
_|PC_Gender=%Gender%|
_|PC_Name=[Fantasy Names.Start]|
_|PC_Weapon=[Weapon]|
_|NPC_Name=[Fantasy Names.Start]|
_|NPC_Occupation=[Miscellaneous.Occupations]|

:Weapon
1,Rapier
2,Axe
3,Spear
4,Scimitar

:Alternate
1,{If~%Gender%=3?|Gender={Dice~1d2}|}
_|PC_Gender=%Gender%|
_|Gender=%PC_Gender%|

:Adventures
1,<b>Sleeper in the Tomb of Dreams</b><br>[Sleeper]
2,<b>Tomb of Terror</b><br>[Terror]
3,<b>The Vale of Shadows</b><br>[ShadowVale]
4,<b>Arcane Tower of Senraven</b><br>[SenRaven]
5,<b>Gates of Blizzard Peak</b><br>[BlizzardPeak]

#Adventures
:Sleeper
1,Strange cultists have stolen relics from clergy of the Raven Queen and taken them deep into their dungeon in the middle of the abandoned burial grounds of the Bloodstar Wars. The clerics aren't strong enough to reclaim them, but they must have the relics back before the eclipse. If they don't perform the ancient ritual with the relics before the moon crosses the sun, legend says that the Sleeper will awaken.<br><br>
_<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> approached the misty, quiet burial grounds with some trepidation at first, having heard many tales of the horrors of the Bloodstar Wars. Then, thinking |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> is a hero, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> mustered all |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> courage and strode boldly forth.<br><br>[Graveyard]<br>
_Deep in the woods behind the graveyard is an ancient crypt -- tunnels below it seem to go on for miles.<br><br>[Dungeon]<br>
_After walking aimlessly for what seems miles, the <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> eventually get their bearings again.<br><br>[Dungeon]<br>
_Final Encounter (Magic)<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> climbed a stairway toward the sound of chanting. As |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> ascended the steps, blood began to rain down from above. Reaching the top step at a run, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> found |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HimselfHerself]</span> in a downpour of blood from holes in the ceiling. Cultists surrounding an open coffin drank in the blood. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> didn't know what was going on, but the cultists held the relics |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> sought in their blood-slick hands.<br>One of the <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>, dripping with blood, raised |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> hands above |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> head and began shouting in tongues. As |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> hoped, the cultists mistook |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HimHer]</span> for an incarnation of their god. They dropped to their knees laying the relics at the <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s feet. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> took the relics, increased the volume of |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> shouting, backed down the stairs. Before the cultists realized they had been duped <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was well on |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> way back to town.<br><br>
_Having successfully completed the adventure, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> headed home to rest.

:Terror
1,The town is plastered with notices declaring a reward to anyone who can recover the lost chalice of Kurgoth from the Tomb of Terror. The Tomb is a dungeon beneath an abandoned graveyard deep in the forest. High Priest Fekis apparently needs the artifact for some purification ritual -- the important thing is that there's a big reward.<br><br>
_<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> headed into Hornfang Forest to search for the mysterious tomb.<br><br>[Forest]<br>
_Another traveler <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> met pointed |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HimHer]</span> in the direction of a graveyard in which the tomb is supposedly located.<br><br>[Forest]<br>
_As night fell, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> found a graveyard near the ruined foundations of a long-abandoned overgrown village.<br><br>[Graveyard]<br>
_Somewhat to <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s surprise, one of the larger mausoleums had "Tomb of Terror" scratched into the stone above the door.<br><br>[Dungeon]<br>
_Final Encounter (Undead)<br>The Chalice of Kurgoth stood on a pedestal behind a pair of tattered skeletons.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> devastated them both with |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> legendary %PC_Weapon%, and they went down without a fuss. It was actually kind of anticlimactic. When |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> returned the chalice to the high priest, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was greatly rewarded.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br><br>
_Having successfully completed the adventure, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> headed home to rest.

:ShadowVale
1,Legend tells of the Vale of Shadows, a lush valley hidden in the mountains that holds a sacred pool with the power to make dreams reality. The Vale is considered a myth, but a delirious elf gave <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> a map before he died. It shows a secret path through the nearby mountains thought to be impassable. Does it lead to a place that can make all <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s dreams come true, or will the journey be a nightmare?
_<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> headed into the mountains, carefully following the map the elf had given her.<br><br>[Mountain]<br>
_Cresting an incline in the narrow trail, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s breath was stolen by the sight of a verdant valley. Birdsong echoed up the cliff walls, and across the vale, a waterfall rushed from the mountains into open space, falling hundreds of feet. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> thought the valley must be uninhabited, but then |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> spied a thin, gray line of smoke from a campfire.<br><br>[Forest]<br>

:SenRaven
1,A wizard has holed up in a tower in the Slugslick Swamp. Based on his choice of location, the specters, and other nasties that have been spotted near his ghostly tower most believe him to be an evil wizard. Is there glory waiting for a righteous adventurer? Are valuable treasures to be had?<br><br> 
_<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> had to cross the mountains to reach the swamp.<br><br>[Mountain]<br>
_<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> slid down the last hill and |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> boots sunk into the muck at the edge of the swamp.<br><br>[Swamp]<br>
_Finally, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> found the Arcane Tower in the heart of the swamp.<br><br>
_<b>Story Encounter</b> (Undead) In the elegant lobby of the tower, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> spotted the wizard at the top of a curved staircase. Before |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> could sprint to the stairs, the wizard summoned a pair of specters to intercept.<br>The specters flanked <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> and, while |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> tried to keep an eye on each of them, they became invisible! Between the rotting spectral touches and life siphons, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> barely defeated them.<br>
_By the time <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was past the specters, the wizard had disappeared deeper into the castle. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> trudged up the stairs after him. <br><br>Castle: [Castle]<br>
_Having searched everywhere else, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> cautiously climbed the spiral staircase to the highest tower in the castle.<br><br>
_<b>Story Encounter</b>(Magic) The wizard had been waiting for <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>. As <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> stepped into the room, magical runes on the floor flashed to life.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s head swam for a minute, but the thought of all the innocent people this evil wizard had harmed gave <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> the strength to break free off his spell.<br><br>
_<b>Final Encounter</b>(Magic) The room crackled with energy as the wizard unfurled his long, thin fingers, unleashing a lightning bolt at <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>.<br>Despite the conditions, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> avoided the blast and, with a fearsome lunge, devastated the evil wizard with |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> legendary %PC_Weapon%. Both the rewards and the glory for this victory were great indeed.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br><br>
_Having successfully completed the adventure, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> headed home to rest.

:BlizzardPeak
1,Once a generation, the Dragon's Tear -- a peculiar comet -- appears in the sky overhead, and the gates of Blizzard Peak swing open. Now the Dragon's Tear once more flickers in the sky, and the glass gates on the mountainside beckon. Can <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> resist the lure of what waits beyond the portal?<br><br>
_Sighting the Dragon's Tear in the night sky, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> headed into the swamp.<br><br>[Swamp]<br>
_On the border between the swamp and forest, several thin, almost skeletal figures danced around a flickering fire. They were adorned with bones and jewelry that rattled and clanked as they chanted and frolicked around the fire.	 
_Story Encounter<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> stepped on a stick, and the loud crack drew their attention. They whooped, hollered, and charged! As they raced toward her, she saw they weren't human at all! They were some kind of demonic half-humans from the elemental chaos.<br>They gave <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> a bit of a beating, but |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> gave back almost as good as |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> got. By questioning one of them, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> learned that they served the Master of the Twisted Caverns beyond the gates of Blizzard Peak. Conveniently, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was already heading in that direction.<br>
_<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> left the forest and entered more mountainous terrain.<br><br>[Mountain]<br>
_The gates were actually quite a bit lower on the mountain side than <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> expected, which might explain why they'd be so hard to find without the guidance of the Dragon's Tear. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> passed through the glass gates and down into the underground city inside.<br><br>[Dungeon]<br>
_Story Encounter<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> saw a staircase leading up to the surface, but it was guarded by a mob of duergar. The dark dwarves opposed |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> passage and demanded to know what |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> was doing here.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> confidently told a story of adventure with plenty of fencing, fighting, torture, revenge, giants, monsters, chases, escapes, true love, and miracles. Duergar are rarely charmed, but these dwarves had not heard such an exciting tale in so long they gladly let <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> pass. They even donated some gold to support |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> further adventures after |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> promised to come back and tell them more next year.<br><br>
_Three-quarters of the way up the mountain, there was cave with distinctively twisted rock formations around the entrance. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> thought it must be the place the dark minions spoke of.	 
_Final Encounter<br>(Magic) A presumedly evil wizard was preparing a ritual, also presumedly evil. Magic circles covered the walls and floor of the cave. Jars of blood and other vile liquids stood on a wobbly looking table near the biggest circle -- which the Master of the Twisted Caverns was mere seconds away from finishing drawing.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> crept up to the table, grabbed a vile jar, and hurled it into the middle of the circle on the floor. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> hastily tossed another at one wall and, as the wizard bellowed in rage at the ruination of his plans, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> walked right up and knocked the wizard out with |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> %PC_Weapon%.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br><br>
_Having successfully completed the adventure, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> headed home to rest.

#Encounters
:Graveyard
1,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Traps) Inside a dank crypt, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> came across a curious-looking sarcophagus chiseled into the stone wall. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> tugged on the door-like lid, triggering a cloud of gas that spewed forth from the vents hidden in the carvings of the sarcophagus.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> squeezed |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> eyes shut, covered |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> mouth, and stumbled out of the noxious cloud. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> held |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> breath until |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> reached the mist-filled-but-clean air of the surface.<br>
2,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> noticed a trio of dubious men huddled next to an open mass grave, picking through and arguing over the division of a small collection of shiny trinkets.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> stomped up to the graverobbers and tried to look menacing as he demanded they hand over the loot -- or else. The dirty men took one look at |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HimHer]</span> and decided "or else," shoving <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> into the deep foul-smelling pit.<br>
3,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_Through a heavy mist, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> spied a cloaked figure skulking around the graveyard and readied |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> %PC_Weapon%. As |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> closed on the suspicious humanoid, it whipped around, revealing itself as a wererat.<br>The wererat snarled through yellowed teeth and stabbed at <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> with its notched short sword. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> avoided the vicious attack and devastated the vile creature, staggering it. Pressing the attack, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> made quick work of the lycanthrope.<br>
4,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Traps) Searching around the perimeter of a sepulcher, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> heard a muffled cry for help coming from inside. Shouting through the loose seal of the giant boulder covering the entrance, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> worked to cooperate with the adventurer trapped on the other side.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> heaved against the boulder with all |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> might. The immense stone shifted just enough for the trapped adventurer to squeeze through. Holding on just a little longer, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> enabled the adventurer to retrieve his sack of treasure, half of which he gratefully offered <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br>
5,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Traps) <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> came across a curious-looking shrine and poked around for hidden compartments and secret treasure. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> found a promising-looking carving and gave it a push.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> made a With a click, a panel gave way beneath <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s feet, opening to a narrow pit. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> caught the edge of the trap door, pulled |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HimselfHerself]</span> up to safety, and decided to go look elsewhere. <br>
6,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_Fervent cries of "Die, vampire spawn!" drew <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> over to a mass grave, where |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> discovered a wild-eyed man plunging a sharpened shovel handle into the lifeless, lime-covered bodies. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> approached with caution.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> hopped down and attempted to calm the clearly unstable gravedigger, who immediately jabbed |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> in the chest, shouting "Take that, bloodsucker!" Not wanting to slay an innocent, but also disliking being struck with a gardening tool, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> clambered out of the grave and bolted.<br>
7,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_While passing through the graveyard, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was surprised by a pair of thugs who'd been hiding behind a couple large monuments. The robbers aimed crossbows at <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> and told |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HimHer]</span> to hand over |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> gold.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> tried to look innocent and told the robbers |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> didn't have any coins. The bluff might have worked if |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> hadn't bumped |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> money pouch while gesturing to further suggest |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> poverty. The crossbow bolts slammed into <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s chest. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> survived and took down both robbers as they struggled to reload.<br>
8,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> came across an interesting monument with a statue tiefling wielding a bow and golden arrow that seemed like someone or something |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> should remember.<br>Figuring that whatever it was |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> was trying to remember might have been treasure-related, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> started digging around the base of the monument. After a few hours of discovering nothing but small rocks and earthworms, |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> pried the gold arrow lose, and continued on |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> way.<br>
9,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Magic) <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> came across a suspicious-looking tiefling skulking around the graveyard.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> briefly interrogated him and learned he had been sent by a nearby temple to investigate the area much like <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> soon continued on, armed with new knowledge about other inhabitants of the graveyard that |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> might encounter.<br>
10,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_Wandering past a long-undisturbed graveyard, overgrown with weeds and choked with sticks, leaves, and other wind-blown debris, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> noticed a shovel caked with fresh dirt.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> wandered around the area, looking for recent activity, but didn''t notice anything until the smugglers showed up. After a hard-fought battle, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> killed the smugglers and took the goods they'd stashed in a well-camouflaged hole.<br>
11,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Undead) <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> came across a foul ghoul gnawing on an unidentifiable bone -- possibly human. Seeing a source of fresher meat, the ghoul attacked!<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> deflected the ghoul's deadly claws long enough to land a killing blow with |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> legendary %PC_Weapon%.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br>
12,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_After burning off thick layers of cobwebs and brushing away a number of moldering bones, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> uncovered an ornate stone sarcophagus. Surely it must have been holding treasure and other secrets.<br>Despite |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> many valiant attempts, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was barely able to budge the lid at all. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> mustered all |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> strength for one last desperate push, shifting the stone slab just enough to release a horrible stench -- and hundreds of tiny spiders. After squashing the entire swarm, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> squeezed |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> spider-bitten arm into the sarcophagus and pulled out a few shiny gems.<br>
	 
:Dungeon
1,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> heard dwarven shouts coming from a tunnel off to |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> left. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> soon reached the dwarves, who explained that a Green Slime was wreaking havoc on their mining operation. In the tight spaces of the mine the slime would easily kill <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> in a head on fight, so |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> had to outsmart it.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> asked the Dwarves to gather up a few rats and then used some rope to tie the rats together. Using this as bait, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> lured the Green Slime right into a pit filled with burning torches. The dwarves gleefully poured lamp oil on the burning slime, which accelerated the incineration process. They rewarded <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> well for devising such a cunning plan.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br>
2,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Undead) "Welcome!" said the vampire as <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> entered an immaculate parlor that was totally out of place in the dank dungeon. "My name is Claboria," said the vampire. "Please stay and play a game with me . . . . I insist," |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> said as |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> motioned toward a gold-and-silver chess set in front of her. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> silently hoped |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> remembered the classic undead chess openings.<br>Halfway through the game, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> noticed that Claboria got fairly angry when losing. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> decided to try a new strategy -- let the vampire win. As Claboria put <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> in checkmate, they had a good laugh, some good wine, and <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> went on |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> way with a solid-gold bishop as a souvenir.<br><b>Fail</b>: <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> quickly realize that Claboria wasn't the sharpest undead chess player in the shed, and easily beat her. Enraged, Claboria hurled a solid-gold pawn at <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> lodged it deeply into <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s leg with her astounding vampiric strength.<br>
3,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Traps) <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> gritted |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> teeth as |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> stumbled through a tripwire in a narrow corridor. When |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> saw the miniature cannon fire straight at |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> chest, there was nothing |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> could to do but brace for the impact.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s armor absorbed most of the blow. Picking up the projectile, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> wondered who would use a gold cannonball.<br>
4,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Giants) <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> had been crawling through a tight passageway for nearly a mile. Upon exiting and stretching out |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> legs, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was beset by an angry storm giant. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> wondered how |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> was going to get out of this one.<br>Thinking quickly, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> dived back into the tight passageway. The giant, unable to reach <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>, raged at |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HimHer]</span> for a few minutes before giving up and wandering away. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> held still a bit to make sure the coast was clear, then hopped back out.<br>
5,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Traps) <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> entered cylindrical room and the door slammed shut behind her. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> then noticed numbered dials next to the door. Above the dials were the words "What is the value of this room?" As |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> pondered this existential question, a copper piece hit |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HimHer]</span> on the head. Then another. Then twenty, then fifty. The room quickly began to fill with copper pieces, and |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> decided |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> had better do some math, and fast.<br>While being pelted with coins, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> approximated the dimensions of the room, picked up a handful of coins, and crunched some numbers. While |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> turned the dials to the answer, the coins reached |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> mouth and began to seriously weigh down on her. The door popped open and <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> rode a wave of coins into the next room. In the better light, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> noticed some of them were gold!<br>
6,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Traps) <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> entered a dead-end marble room. There, under a devious trap, laid a recently killed adventurer. From what <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> could tell, the giant emerald used as bait would be |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HisHers]</span> if |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> could lift the device.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> hefted the trap out of the way, claimed the flawless emerald, and gave |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> fallen comrade in dungeoneering a proper burial.<br>
7,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> had been walking down a hallway for a while when |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> noticed that all its walls were engraved with the symbols of Yeenoghu, the demon lord of gnolls. Hearing scrabbling up ahead, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> pulled |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> legendary %PC_Weapon% and charged into the impending gnoll horde.<br>Taking the gnolls by surprise, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> killed three of them before they had even finished drawing their weapons. From the rear, the gnoll huntmaster drew back his bow as his horrible horde assailed <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>. took many arrows fighting |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> way through the gnoll mass to get to the huntmaster. Knowing that gnolls show no mercy, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> treated them in kind. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> sent the demon worshipers to visit their horrible god.<br>
8,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_Detecting fresh air, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> found an opening twenty feet overhead. Suddenly, a dead gazelle fell through the hole.<br>The gazelle was followed by a pack of ravenous wolves that didn't seem to notice <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> waited for the wolves to become distracted by their meal and then struck. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> had the hides made into armor when |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> got back to town.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received 95 XP.<br>
9,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_An ogre warhulk charged out of nowhere toward <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> would have been bashed to smithereens, but |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> instead stepped slightly to the side, stretched one foot out into the ogre's path, tightly closed |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> eyes, and waited for the ogre to trip headfirst onto a large stalagmite. The stupidity of ogres is legendary.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br>
10,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Undead) The angry ghost of some long dead adventurer was lurking about. It hovered over a skeleton decked out in a dusty (but clearly top-quality) suit of delver's leather.<br>Leading with |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> courage and finishing with |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> legendary %PC_Weapon%, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> sent the phantom warrior to its final resting place.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br>
11,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_The statue room seemed a bit out of place here in the dungeon. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> took a short rest in the gallery filled with statues of brave adventurers. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> noticed that some of the equipment at the statues' feet was a little too real -- this was no art display! As <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> franticly gathered |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> things, the medusa was already sneaking up on her, looking to add <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> to its collection.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> felt |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> body stiffen under the medusa's gaze. The medusa drew back |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> bow and fired an arrow into <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s chest. As the medusa closed in to finish <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> shook off |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> affliction and ran from the room.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br>
12,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> saw a kitten shaking in the corner of a small room. When |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> went to pet its tentacle, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> noticed two odd things. First, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> hand passed through the air where |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> eyes could have sworn the kitten should have been and, second, kittens shouldn't have tentacles. A young displacer beast!<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> devastated the beast mightily! The displacer beast gazed upon |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HimHer]</span> with pleading eyes as it breathed its last breath. Displacer beast veal should sell well, if only <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> could figure out where the carcass was.<br>
13,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Undead) <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> came across a horde of decrepit skeletons shambling down a corridor toward her.<br>Luckily, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> had literally just avoided tripping a boulder trap a second ago. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> went back, tripped it intentionally, and ducked into a side passage. The sound of crunching bones was quite satisfying.<br>
14,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Undead) A zombie, mumbling incoherently, made its way toward <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> . . .<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> had no trouble getting the jump on the slow moving zombie and made short work of it with |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> %PC_Weapon%.<br> 
15,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_A group of adventurers was sitting at a table, laughing and having a good time. As <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> approached, |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> realized they were playing three-dragon ante! |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> promptly asked to join in.<br>The size of <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s stack dwindled steadily, until out of sheer frustration |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> decided it was time to start cheating. Unfortunately, one of the more perceptive players at the table noticed this, and the resulting fistfight left <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> battered and bruised (and slightly richer).<br>
16,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_A wererat leaped out from the corner, snarling viciously! <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> ducked under its initial assault, turned . . .<br> . . . and promptly devastated it with |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> legendary %PC_Weapon%. The wererat twitched feebly for a few seconds, then perished.<br>
17,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Undead) Reaching the end of a corridor, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> discovered a small room stocked with brooms and mops that looked strangely like a cleaning closet. Now that |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> thought about it, this dungeon was rather clean. Then again, |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> didn't have much time to think about it -- |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> was more concerned with the skeleton lunging at her!<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> ducked and the skeleton's bony fingers just raked |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> shoulder. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> counterattack, on the other hand, scattered the skeleton into pieces.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br>
18,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Constructs) An iron defender came marching up the hallway towards <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>!<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> went toe to toe with the defender. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> eventually came out ahead, but was definitely worse for wear.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received 175 XP and 58 gold.
19,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_How the halfling prowlers thought they could keep their presence hidden while their human berserker companion kept asking them questions was not the issue, so much as it was what should be done about the lot of them as they passed by the room in which <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> had recently discovered some valuable items.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> burst out of the room, knocking a halfling to the floor with the door. Then |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> missed the berserker so widely that he burst out laughing. The other halfling was not so amused and let <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> have it with his short sword. Outnumbered and at a clear disadvantage, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> fled, grabbing the halfling's coinpurse on the way out.<br>
20,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Traps) <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> found a room with moss-covered brick walls and a treasure chest locked behind an iron grate.<br>Carefully searching the room, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> noticed that the moss on one of the bricks on the wall behind the chest was scraped off. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> took out |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> 10-foot pole and threaded it through the bars to tap the mossless brick. The brick moved, and by leaning on the stick, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was able to unlock the gate! The treasure chest itself wasn''t even locked.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br>

:Forest
1,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_While |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> was busy being chased by a pack of wolves, a rocky cliff wall decided it should appear directly in front of her.<br>Without slowing down, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> practically ran up the wall, climbing to safety as the wolves skidded to a halt below. Oddly, there was a pouch of gold stuck in some brambles on the edge of the small cliff. It must have gotten caught there when its owner fell down on this very spot sometime in the past.<br>
2,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_When a spitting drake came crashing through the leaves straight for her, naturally <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> killed it. When an axe-bearing dwarf came charging out of the same leaves a minute later, he was pretty mad at <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> for killing his prey.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> tried to convince the dwarf that the beast had died spontaneously, but the obvious marks from |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> legendary %PC_Weapon% made the truth kind of obvious. The dwarf took the corpse by the tail and stormed off into the woods.<br>
3,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_Many fights have defining moments -- that one strike that turns the tide or reveals the difference in between combatant's skills. In <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s fight against two human bandits, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> had just such a moment. Outnumbered with a steep dropoff behind her, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> felt death, or at least a severely painful injury, closing in on her.<br>Crouching down, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> took some dirt in one hand and tightened |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> grip on |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> legendary %PC_Weapon%. In an abrupt burst of speed, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> threw the dirt in the eyes of one bandit and devastated the other. Spinning past them like a dervish, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> caught them both dead center and finished the job.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br>
4,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_It was not a pleasant sight when the stone came flying out of the bushes at <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s head.<br>It did no harm, of course -- but still, it was not pleasant to see it coming straight for her. The easy fight against the two goblin blackblades did somewhat make up for it, however, as they carried some valuables on them.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received an <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br>
5,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_As <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> approached a coach parked in the road, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> heard someone softly crying. It was a little girl whose favorite pet had leaped out of |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> family's carriage and scampered up a tree. The family was worried about loitering in the forest for too long, and none of them could scale the tree.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> had a very difficult time climbing up the tree. When |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> was only a few feet up, a couple of goblins came out of the woods to rob the family. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> tried to climb down but ended up falling on top of one of them, nearly getting |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HimselfHerself]</span> run through by the creature's sword. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> was further wounded chasing the second one off. In the end the pet was rescued, the family spared, and at least one of the goblins was looted. It could have gone worse.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br>
6,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was startled when a dagger plunged into the ground mere inches from |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> foot. Looking up |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> saw something hanging from a branch high in a tree.<br>How it got there or what it was, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> will never know. The tree was especially difficult to climb, and |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> failed to climb past the lowest branches.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br>
7,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_Sounds of hammering and sawing led <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> to dozen human lackeys a constructing a fort under the direction of an evil wizard. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> assumed the wizard was evil because he had imprisoned an evistro in a very heavy iron cage. Something had to be done.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> boldly kicked down the door to the fort (it wasn't actually attached to the wall yet, just sort of leaning up against it) and began slaying minions left and right. The mage released the evistro, and faced with both the wizard and the demon, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> realized it was time to flee. The next morning, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> reported the encampment to human soldiers in a nearby fort and they paid |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HimHer]</span> for the information.<br>
8,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_Two hobgoblin warriors trained as battlemates from birth accosted <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> and demanded a toll -- in blood! At their command a brutish, muscular bugbear with a wicked morningstar maneuvered in to deliver <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> a skullthumping when |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> refused to pay.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> used |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> legendary %PC_Weapon% on one hobgoblin, but its battlemate's shield protected it. The bugbear, moving with a grace and speed that seemed impossible for such a big, hairy thing, slipped behind <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> and clocked |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HimHer]</span> good with its morningstar. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s legendary %PC_Weapon%, however, was too much for the goblins, and |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> brought them all down.<br>
9,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_Hearing about a dire wolf that was plaguing the local hunters, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> had decided to track it down. The trail led into the forest where |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> cornered the beast in its den.<br>After that, it was almost no trouble to slay the beast and bring peace to the locals. It was nice of them to reward |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HimHer]</span> for |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> trouble.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br>
10,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Magic) In the middle of a fight with an orc eye of gruumsh, the orc tried to strike fear into <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> with its eye of wrath ability.<br>It worked, and <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> ran away, pathetically.<br>
11,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Constructs) While exploring one of the forest's many ancient and abandoned sites, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> came face to face with an iron cobra. The homunculus's head drifted sinuously left and right, swaying in an almost mesmeric rhythm as it prepared to strike.<br>A little afraid of the swaying serpent, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> took a half-hearted swing at it with |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> legendary %PC_Weapon%. A faint effort rarely yields results, and the only result of this one was a bite from a mechanical snake. The old construct's poison had long since dried up but its jaw had locked in place when it bit. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> had to bash it off with a rock.<br>
12,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> came to a ravine with spider webs stretched among the trees. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> was thinking better of continuing and had turned back when an ettercap fang guard and a deathjump spider blocked |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> way.<br>The spider leaped on <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>, and the ettercap maneuvered for a flanking attack. As |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> fought, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was bitten by both opponents, but |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> shrugged off their poison and devastated them -- first one, then the other. Before |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> left, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> cut down an object that caught |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> eye suspended in the webs.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br>
13,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Dragons) As <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> scouted out the base of a steep, rocky slope looking for the best way up, a big, red, scaly ragedrake came barreling at |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HimHer]</span> through the trees. A delighted kobold with two swords scrambled along behind.<br>While <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was busy fending off the drake's claws and fangs, the kobold slipped around behind |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HimHer]</span> for a dirty and highly effective twin slash. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was sliced up on one side and ripped down on the other. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> devastated the kobold and then turned |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> weapon on the drake. It got angrier and stronger the more <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> hurt it, and by the time |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> finished it, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> was a mess.

:Mountain
1,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was trying to find |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> way back home and saw two people arguing. They were almost to the point of drawing their weapons. From what <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> could hear, it seemed as though they were two brothers who had defended themselves against a thief and were now arguing over who should get what. Can <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> get these two brothers to see reason?<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> tried to convince the two that violence wasn't the answer. They disagreed -- and chased <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> off with their swords swinging!<br>
2,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_While <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was looking for |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> next adventure, the next adventure was also looking for her! Large boulders careened down the mountainside -- headed right for <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>! There was no time to escape!<br>One large boulder hit <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> right in the shoulder, but |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> shrugged it off. Then |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> noticed a pair of hobgoblins who were sending more |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> way! <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> took off after them! A few minutes later <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> strolled off counting the hobgoblins' loot.<br>
3,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_Coming around a bend, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> heard a cry for help. Running toward it, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> saw a young man hanging off the side of the mountain. How did he get there? No time to figure that out -- time to be heroic!<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> almost managed to pull the young man up, but instead both went tumbling down the mountainside! Eventually, they came to a stop with a crunch and a yelp of pain. The young man broke his leg and <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> carried him out of the ravine. An aspiring adventurer himself, the young man rewarded <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> with some of the spoils from his last quest.<br>
4,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_A local farmer needed an escort through the mountain valley to ensure |Gender=%NPC_Gender%| [HisHer] harvest made it to market. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> expected trouble, and |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> wasn't disappointed. A young man appeared from out of nowhere -- an ambush! The young man moved to attack the farmer.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> and the young man fought, and it was clear that <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was the better of the two. The young man said, "Don't kill me! I'm starving and I don't know what else to do!" The farmer took a long look at the kid and said, "If you had just asked, I would have given you some. Get lost!" The farmer sold |Gender=%NPC_Gender%| [HisHer] harvest in town and gave <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> a portion of |Gender=%NPC_Gender%| [HisHer] profits.<br>
5,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> found a large treasure chest hastily buried on the side of the mountain path. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> had quite the load to haul back down the mountainside. If |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> wasn't in such a hurry, |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> could take all day. But, alas, several raiders wanted their goods back, and the chase was on!<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> struggled to keep ahead of the raiders. When the arrows landed in |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> back <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> knew it was time to face facts -- |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> wasn't going to outrun them carrying this much weight. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> poured out some of the gold which sped |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> up and slowed the raiders down. This allowed |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> to get |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> newly acquired goods safely to town.<br>
6,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> discovered an opening appeared to be thirty or forty feet above her. Such a climb meant that it would be unlikely that anyone would have attempted to go looking inside . . . <br>When <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> had climbed halfway up, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> lost |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> footing. The fall gave <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> just enough time to have second thoughts.<br>
7,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_Sometimes, it is great to be a hero. Other times, it is great to be a fast hero. Especially when trying to outrun a goblin horde. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was managing to keep a fair amount of distance between |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HimselfHerself]</span> and the horde -- until |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> found the end of the road. Turning back not being an option, it was time for <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> to jump off a cliff . . . hopefully into the river below.<br><br>*ker-THUNK* -- <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> reached the water, but only barely. Luckily, the rocks below the water's surface broke |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> fall (and possibly |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> leg).<br> 
8,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(rare)<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> came across a wise old man. "I knew you would be here," he said. "I have something to share."<br><br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> listened to the wise man. "Respect should be shown to those who have earned it." Just then, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> felt the end of a sword pressed lightly into |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> back. The old man continued, "But, you should trust no one." <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> raised |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> arms, and the rogue stepped from behind her. "This lesson won't cost you . . . this time." With that <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was struck hard in the back of the head. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> woke up with a headache surprised to still be in the possession of all |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> belongings.<br>
9,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> found a hidden entrance to an abandoned mine. Unable to overcome |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> desire to acquire, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> entered the mine. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> walked through the opening, admiring the decent condition the place was in (ignoring the spider webs, of course) -- when all of a sudden |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> heard a *crack!* And a rumble. And a collapse.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> ran back toward the mine opening, only to be struck by a collapsing support beam. It took several hours for |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HimHer]</span> to find a way out, but along the way |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> found a few gold nuggets. Although |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> escaped, she's going to need to have that arm looked at when |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> gets back.<br>
10,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_Those hobgoblins just won't go away! And now they are resorting to poison-tipped arrows . . . one of which just pierced <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s shoulder. Up on the mountainside, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> is pretty far from help.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> shrugged off the poison, ripping the arrow out, and used it as a crude weapon against the hobgoblins!<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br>
11,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_In a mountaintop village, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was having a good night in a local tavern. The strongest person in town challenged all takers to an arm-wrestling contest. "I'm the strongest person in this town," he bellows, "and I can beat any of you in arm-wrestling!" <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> stepped up to the challenge.<br>It seemed like the entire town had gathered around the table for this epic test of strength. After a few tense moments of back-and-forth action, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> slammed |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> opponent's fist down to the table. Victory -- and a small amount of gold -- was hers!<br>
12,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> found a hidden entrance to an abandoned mine. Unable to overcome |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> desire to acquire, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> entered the mine. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> walked through the opening, admiring the decent condition the place was in (ignoring the spider webs, of course) -- when all of a sudden |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> heard a *crack!* And a rumble. And a collapse.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> ran back toward the mine opening, only to be struck by a collapsing support beam. It took several hours for |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HimHer]</span> to find a way out, but along the way |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> found a few gold nuggets. Although |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> escaped, she's going to need to have that arm looked at when |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> gets back.<br>
13,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Dragons) A curious outcropping of rock caught <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s attention. Its moss had been entirely scraped and singed off. When |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> left the trail to take a closer look, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> could see a dark recess hidden behind the rocks. Moving carefully, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> took a step toward the cave . . . then froze as a sudden cacophony erupted from within. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> had no time to respond before a swarm of dragon whelps, upset at being disturbed, rushed straight at her!<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> readied |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> %PC_Weapon% just as the swarm of dragon whelps descended upon her. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> desperately tried to defend |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HimselfHerself]</span> amidst the madness of wings and claws, but there were just too many of them. Bleeding and burnt, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> finally managed to break free from the whelps by rolling down into a steep ravine. The threat to their home averted, the dragon whelps returned to their cave. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> wisely decided not to follow suit.<br>
14,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_Exploring an abandoned mine, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> heard footsteps coming from behind. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> asked, "who goes?" An elvish man approached. "Finally, a friendly voice," he replied. "I can use your help, if you are willing."<br>"I'm doing well enough alone, thank you very much!" said <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> defiantly. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> didn't need anyone else. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was so busy doing well enough alone, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> didn't notice |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> was stepping right into a pit. "Um, help?" <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s plea was only met with laughter.<br>

:Swamp
1,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_<span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> was lost in the swamp. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> had found |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> way to a road, but which road |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> didn't know. There |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> met some well guarded and rich-looking merchants who didn't appear to be in the mood to help lost adventurers.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> tried, but the merchants were not interested in talking. They called |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HimHer]</span> several unpleasant names as well, focusing their verbal attacks on the prestige differences between high class merchants and swamp-trudging monster-molesting adventurers.<br>
2,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_Sitting on top of a young gnoll |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> had just subdued, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> heard the cries of more gnolls approaching. Not wanting the gnoll to be able to chase her, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> pulled out a rope to tie it up with.<br>Working quickly, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> bound the gnoll tightly with difficult knots and blindfolded it so it could not see which way |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> went. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> had time to relieve it of its valuables before racing off into the swamp.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br>
3,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_Why the two young lovers were traveling in the swamp was none of <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s business. Nor was their dreadful lack of protection from all sorts of monsters. It was a miracle they were still unharmed. Still |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> felt bad just leaving them there, shouting at each other at the top of their lungs. Surely some hungry creature would hear them and come for them soon. So |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> tried to defuse the argument and get them on their way.<br>Everything <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> said only made the fight worse, and soon the lovers were angry with |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HimHer]</span> as well as each other. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> fled the scene before something deadly came by.<br>
4,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_In order to spy on the gnolls, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> had disguised |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HimselfHerself]</span> as one and infiltrated their camp. They were deciding who they should attack next -- the nice people in the town on the edge of the swamp, or the kobolds who had begun to invade their territory. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> spoke up.<br>Opening |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> mouth was a big mistake, and the gnolls instantly saw through <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s disguise. They chased |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HimHer]</span> from the camp. Fearing the humans were a greater threat if they could infiltrate the gnoll camp so easily, they decided to attack the townspeople.<br>
5,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_While climbing through the branches of a cypress tree, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> heard the approach of several unpleasant voices and the sloshing of feet through the swamp. It was a pack of foulspawn! |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> stood frozen in a very awkward position, but |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> dared not move lest |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> give |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HimselfHerself]</span> away as the monsters drew near.<br>|Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HisHer]}</span> arms began to ache, but |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> held on while the foulspawn berserker got into an argument with one of the manglers. As |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> grip began to slip, the seer interrupted the fight and ordered them all to move on. They were still only a few yards away when <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s arms gave out and |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> dropped into the water with a loud splash. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> didn't look back to see if the foulspawn were chasing, but the distortion blast that slammed into |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> back implied that they were.<br>

:Castle
1,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Magic) <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> wandered into the library and found |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HimselfHerself]</span> drawn to a book on a dust-covered shelf. The book was written in an ancient, arcane language.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> studied the text and referenced several other books in the library. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> was able to fully translate one of the passages. It was an incantation to make one's skin as hard as stone. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> read the passage aloud and |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> body transformed. Though it remained flexible |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> skin became as hard as granite. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> took one of the books too, to sell back in town.<br> 
2,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_Making |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> way through the impossibly many rooms of the wizard's tower, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> found . . . more rooms. Every door |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> opened led into another drab, empty room. Even when |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> tried to backtrack |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> way out, each door opened into the same featureless room.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> had had enough of this. It had been hours of room after room of the same nothing. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> was going mad. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> clawed at the wall until |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> fingers bled. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> banged |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> head against the floor until |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> vision was blurry. There seemed to be no way out. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> gave up and let sleep take her. When |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> awoke |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> was in a different room! |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> grabbed a few items of value and slowly walked towards the door. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> sheepishly opened the door and, to |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> disbelief, found a room that |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> recognized from near the entrance to the tower. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HeShe]}</span> could find |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> way out from here.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br>
3,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_There were some areas of the castle where the guards wouldn't allow <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> to enter. Knowing that true adventure could only be found in those areas, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> decided to sneak past the guards.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> waited for the moment to be right. The guards were locked in heated debate about what to do with their latest prisoner. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> stuck to the shadows. Each of |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> footfalls in time with the guards' shouts, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> made it to the doorway. Pressing |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> luck, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> managed to lift one of the guard's coin purses and slip through completely unnoticed.<br>
4,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Undead) While walking past the hedge maze, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> saw some motion in the distance. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> made |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> way over to the royal crypt and found a ghoul feasting on the remains of an exhumed noble.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> drew |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> %PC_Weapon% and charged the ghoul. The ghoul turned to face <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>. The two collided, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> devastated and the ghoul clawed. The ghoul's attacks were no match for <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s quick reflexes, but one of <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s attacks took the ghoul's head clean off. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> helped |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HimselfHerself]</span> to some of the valuables in the sarcophagus and headed back toward the castle.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received an <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br>
5,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Undead) <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> came upon a large, ornate mirror in the gallery. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HisHer]}</span> reflection seemed to be moving with a will of its own.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s reflection beckoned |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HimHer]</span> closer to the mirror, and |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> took a hesitant step toward it. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HisHer]}</span> reflection took the form of a beautiful woman and again it motioned for <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> to come closer. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> took another step toward the mirror in disbelief. The reflection opened its hands and gold coins spilled out from them, through the mirror, and onto the gallery floor. Again it beckoned for <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> to come closer. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> took the last step to the mirror and reached in to touch |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> reflection. It was only then that the reflection revealed its true form -- an ugly, twisted apparition wanting nothing more than to drain <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s life force. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">{Cap~[HisHer]}</span> hand was stuck in the mirror, grayed and withered, and the necrosis crept up |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> arm. With all |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> might, and a great deal of pain, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> pulled |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HisHer]</span> arm from the mirror and smashed the haunted glass to the ground.<br>
6,|PC_Treasure=[Equipment.Start]|
_(Traps) While exploring the castle's vast underground laboratory, <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> came upon a large clockwork chest. It was part box, part machine, and <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> couldn't resist trying to find out what was inside. <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> figured one of the three levers on the front of the chest was bound to open it.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> pulled the first lever and sharpened gears flew from the chest. They sliced through <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s flesh and stuck in the wall behind him. |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> refused to let the pain stop |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HimHer]</span> so |Gender=%PC_Gender%| <span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> pulled the middle lever. Poisoned darts shot from the lid and into <span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span>'s shoulder, chest, and neck. Despite the numbness, |Gender=%PC_Gender%|<span style="color:red">[HeShe]</span> mustered the strength to pull the rightmost lever and the box sprang open, revealing its treasures.<br><span style="color=blue">%PC_Name%</span> received a <span style="color=blue">%PC_Treasure%</span>.<br>